nbsFecpmMib.name: nbsFecpmMib
nbsFecpmMib.contactinfo: For technical support, please contact your service channel
nbsFecpmMib.description: OTN Forward Error Correction (FEC) Performance Monitoring and user-controlled statistics

nbsFecpmCurrentGrp.name: nbsFecpmCurrentGrp
nbsFecpmCurrentGrp.description: Subtotals and statistics for sample now underway

nbsFecpmHistoricGrp.name: nbsFecpmHistoricGrp
nbsFecpmHistoricGrp.description: Totals and final statistics for a previous sample

nbsFecpmThresholdsEntry.name: nbsFecpmThresholdsEntry
nbsFecpmThresholdsEntry.description: Performance monitoring thresholds for a particular interface

nbsFecpmThresholdsInterval.name: nbsFecpmThresholdsInterval
nbsFecpmThresholdsInterval.description: Indicates the periodicity to which these thresholds apply

nbsFecpmThresholdsBitErrCor.name: nbsFecpmThresholdsBitErrCor
nbsFecpmThresholdsBitErrCor.description: Persistent. The number of Bit Errors Corrected which, if met or exceeded at the end of the nbsFecpmThresholdsInterval period, should trigger the nbsFecpmTrapsBitErrCor event notification. The reserved value 0 disables notifications for this event.

nbsFecpmThresholdsByteErrCor.name: nbsFecpmThresholdsByteErrCor
nbsFecpmThresholdsByteErrCor.description: Persistent. The number of Byte Errors Corrected which, if met or exceeded at the end of the nbsFecpmThresholdsInterval period, should trigger the nbsFecpmTrapsByteErrCor event notification. The reserved value 0 disables notifications for this event.

nbsFecpmThresholdsCorBit0to1.name: nbsFecpmThresholdsCorBit0to1
nbsFecpmThresholdsCorBit0to1.description: Persistent. The number of '0' bits corrected to '1' which, if met or exceeded at the end of the nbsFecpmThresholdsInterval period, should trigger the nbsFecpmTrapsCorBit0to1 event notification. The reserved value 0 disables notifications for this event.

nbsFecpmThresholdsCorBit1to0.name: nbsFecpmThresholdsCorBit1to0
nbsFecpmThresholdsCorBit1to0.description: Persistent. The number of '1' bits corrected to '0' which, if met or exceeded at the end of the nbsFecpmThresholdsInterval period, should trigger the nbsFecpmTrapsCorBit1to0 event notification. The reserved value 0 disables notifications for this event.

nbsFecpmThresholdsUncorWords.name: nbsFecpmThresholdsUncorWords
nbsFecpmThresholdsUncorWords.description: Persistent. The number of Uncorrectable Words which, if met or exceeded at the end of the nbsFecpmThresholdsInterval period, should trigger the nbsFecpmTrapsUncorWords event notification. The reserved value 0 disables notifications for this event.

nbsFecpmCurrentSysDate.name: nbsFecpmCurrentSysDate
nbsFecpmCurrentSysDate.description: The current (today's) UTC date, represented by an eight digit decimal number: yyyymmdd

nbsFecpmCurrentSysTime.name: nbsFecpmCurrentSysTime
nbsFecpmCurrentSysTime.description: The current (now's) UTC time, represented by a six digit decimal number in the format hhmmss

nbsFecpmCurrentTable.name: nbsFecpmCurrentTable
nbsFecpmCurrentTable.description: All FEC Performance Monitoring statistics for the nbsFecpmCurrentInterval now underway.

nbsFecpmCurrentEntry.name: nbsFecpmCurrentEntry
nbsFecpmCurrentEntry.description: FEC Performance Monitoring statistics for a specific port/ interface and nbsFecpmCurrentInterval.

nbsFecpmCurrentDate.name: nbsFecpmCurrentDate
nbsFecpmCurrentDate.description: The date (UTC) this interval began, represented by an eight digit decimal number: yyyymmdd

nbsFecpmCurrentTime.name: nbsFecpmCurrentTime
nbsFecpmCurrentTime.description: The time (UTC) this interval began, represented by a six digit decimal number: hhmmss

nbsFecpmCurrentBitErrCor.name: nbsFecpmCurrentBitErrCor
nbsFecpmCurrentBitErrCor.description: The number of Bit Errors Corrected in this interval so far; it may be the sum of nbsFecpmCurrentCorBit0to1 and nbsFecpmCurrentCorBit1to0.

nbsFecpmCurrentByteErrCor.name: nbsFecpmCurrentByteErrCor
nbsFecpmCurrentByteErrCor.description: The number of Byte Errors Corrected in this interval so far. The reserved value 0xFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFF indicates not supported.

nbsFecpmCurrentCorBit0to1.name: nbsFecpmCurrentCorBit0to1
nbsFecpmCurrentCorBit0to1.description: The number of '0' bits corrected to '1' so far. The reserved value 0xFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFF indicates there is a single number for all bit corrections combined, see nbsFecpmCurrentBitErrCor.

nbsFecpmCurrentCorBit1to0.name: nbsFecpmCurrentCorBit1to0
nbsFecpmCurrentCorBit1to0.description: The number of '1' bits corrected to '0' so far. The reserved value 0xFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFF indicates there is a single number for all bit corrections combined, see nbsFecpmCurrentBitErrCor.

nbsFecpmCurrentUncorWords.name: nbsFecpmCurrentUncorWords
nbsFecpmCurrentUncorWords.description: The number of Uncorrectable Words so far

nbsFecpmHistoricTable.name: nbsFecpmHistoricTable
nbsFecpmHistoricTable.description: All FEC Performance Monitoring statistics for past nbsFecpmHistoricInterval periods.

nbsFecpmHistoricEntry.name: nbsFecpmHistoricEntry
nbsFecpmHistoricEntry.description: FEC Performance Monitoring statistics for a specific port/ interface and nbsFecpmHistoricInterval.

nbsFecpmHistoricInterval.name: nbsFecpmHistoricInterval
nbsFecpmHistoricInterval.description: Indicates the sampling period of statistic

nbsFecpmHistoricSample.name: nbsFecpmHistoricSample
nbsFecpmHistoricSample.description: Indicates the sample number of this statistic. The most recent sample is numbered 1, the next previous 2, and so on until the oldest sample.

nbsFecpmHistoricDate.name: nbsFecpmHistoricDate
nbsFecpmHistoricDate.description: The date (UTC) the interval began, represented by an eight digit decimal number: yyyymmdd

nbsFecpmHistoricTime.name: nbsFecpmHistoricTime
nbsFecpmHistoricTime.description: The time (UTC) the interval began, represented by a six digit decimal number: hhmmss

nbsFecpmHistoricBitErrCor.name: nbsFecpmHistoricBitErrCor
nbsFecpmHistoricBitErrCor.description: The final count of Bit Errors Corrected for this interval; it may be the sum of nbsFecpmHistoricCorBit0to1 and nbsFecpmHistoricCorBit1to0.

nbsFecpmHistoricByteErrCor.name: nbsFecpmHistoricByteErrCor
nbsFecpmHistoricByteErrCor.description: The final count of Byte Errors Corrected in this interval. The reserved value 0xFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFF indicates not supported.

nbsFecpmHistoricCorBit0to1.name: nbsFecpmHistoricCorBit0to1
nbsFecpmHistoricCorBit0to1.description: The final count of '0' bits corrected to '1' in this interval. The reserved value 0xFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFF indicates there is a single number for all bit corrections combined, see nbsFecpmHistoricBitErrCor.

nbsFecpmHistoricCorBit1to0.name: nbsFecpmHistoricCorBit1to0
nbsFecpmHistoricCorBit1to0.description: The final count of '1' bits corrected to '0' in this interval. The reserved value 0xFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFF indicates there is a single number for all bit corrections combined, see nbsFecpmHistoricBitErrCor.

nbsFecpmHistoricUncorWords.name: nbsFecpmHistoricUncorWords
nbsFecpmHistoricUncorWords.description: The final number of Uncorrectable Words in this interval

nbsFecpmRunningTable.name: nbsFecpmRunningTable
nbsFecpmRunningTable.description: All FEC Performance Monitoring statistics since boot-up.

nbsFecpmRunningEntry.name: nbsFecpmRunningEntry
nbsFecpmRunningEntry.description: FEC Performance Monitoring statistics for a specific port/ interface.

nbsFecpmRunningDate.name: nbsFecpmRunningDate
nbsFecpmRunningDate.description: The date (UTC) of boot-up, represented by an eight digit decimal number: yyyymmdd

nbsFecpmRunningTime.name: nbsFecpmRunningTime
nbsFecpmRunningTime.description: The time (UTC) of boot-up, represented by a six digit decimal number: hhmmss

nbsFecpmRunningBitErrCor.name: nbsFecpmRunningBitErrCor
nbsFecpmRunningBitErrCor.description: The total count of Bit Errors Corrected since boot-up; it may be the sum of nbsFecpmRunningCorBit0to1 and nbsFecpmRunningCorBit1to0.

nbsFecpmRunningByteErrCor.name: nbsFecpmRunningByteErrCor
nbsFecpmRunningByteErrCor.description: The total count of Byte Errors Corrected since boot-up. The reserved value 0xFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFF indicates not supported.

nbsFecpmRunningCorBit0to1.name: nbsFecpmRunningCorBit0to1
nbsFecpmRunningCorBit0to1.description: The total count of '0' bits corrected to '1' since boot-up. The reserved value 0xFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFF indicates there is a single number for all bit corrections combined, see nbsFecpmRunningBitErrCor.

nbsFecpmRunningCorBit1to0.name: nbsFecpmRunningCorBit1to0
nbsFecpmRunningCorBit1to0.description: The total count of '1' bits corrected to '0' since boot-up. The reserved value 0xFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFF indicates there is a single number for all bit corrections combined, see nbsFecpmRunningBitErrCor.

nbsFecpmRunningUncorWords.name: nbsFecpmRunningUncorWords
nbsFecpmRunningUncorWords.description: The total number of Uncorrectable Words since boot-up

nbsFecStatsTable.name: nbsFecStatsTable
nbsFecStatsTable.description: FEC statistics managed at the user's discretion. These statistics may be started, stopped, and cleared whenever the user desires without affecting the normal performance monitoring activity.

nbsFecStatsEntry.name: nbsFecStatsEntry
nbsFecStatsEntry.description: User-controlled FEC statistics for a specific port/interface.

nbsFecStatsDate.name: nbsFecStatsDate
nbsFecStatsDate.description: The (UTC) date the user began statistics collection, represented by an eight digit decimal number: yyyymmdd

nbsFecStatsTime.name: nbsFecStatsTime
nbsFecStatsTime.description: The (UTC) time the user began statistics collection, represented by a six digit decimal number: hhmmss

nbsFecStatsSpan.name: nbsFecStatsSpan
nbsFecStatsSpan.description: The amount of time (deci-sec) statistics collection has been underway since nbsFecStatsDate and nbsFecStatsTime, or if stopped, the duration of the prior collection.

nbsFecStatsState.name: nbsFecStatsState
nbsFecStatsState.description: Writing 'stopped' to this object stops (pauses) FEC statistics collection. Writing 'counting' to this object starts (resumes) FEC statistics collection. Writing 'clearing' to this object clears all statistical counters.

nbsFecStatsBitErrCor.name: nbsFecStatsBitErrCor
nbsFecStatsBitErrCor.description: The total count of Bit Errors Corrected since boot-up; it may be the sum of nbsFecStatsCorBit0to1 and nbsFecStatsCorBit1to0.

nbsFecStatsByteErrCor.name: nbsFecStatsByteErrCor
nbsFecStatsByteErrCor.description: The total count of Byte Errors Corrected since boot-up. The reserved value 0xFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFF indicates not supported.

nbsFecStatsCorBit0to1.name: nbsFecStatsCorBit0to1
nbsFecStatsCorBit0to1.description: The total count of '0' bits corrected to '1' since boot-up. The reserved value 0xFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFF indicates there is a single number for all bit corrections combined, see nbsFecStatsBitErrCor.

nbsFecStatsCorBit1to0.name: nbsFecStatsCorBit1to0
nbsFecStatsCorBit1to0.description: The total count of '1' bits corrected to '0' since boot-up. The reserved value 0xFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFF indicates there is a single number for all bit corrections combined, see nbsFecStatsBitErrCor.

nbsFecStatsUncorWords.name: nbsFecStatsUncorWords
nbsFecStatsUncorWords.description: The total number of Uncorrectable Words since boot-up

nbsFecpmTrapsBitErrCor.name: nbsFecpmTrapsBitErrCor
nbsFecpmTrapsBitErrCor.description: Sent at the conclusion of an nbsFecpmThresholdsInterval if nbsFecpmThresholdsBitErrCor is non-zero and less than or equal to nbsFecpmCurrentBitErrCor.

nbsFecpmTrapsByteErrCor.name: nbsFecpmTrapsByteErrCor
nbsFecpmTrapsByteErrCor.description: Sent at the conclusion of an nbsFecpmThresholdsInterval if nbsFecpmThresholdsByteErrCor is non-zero and less than or equal to nbsFecpmCurrentByteErrCor.

nbsFecpmTrapsCorBit0to1.name: nbsFecpmTrapsCorBit0to1
nbsFecpmTrapsCorBit0to1.description: Sent at the conclusion of an nbsFecpmThresholdsInterval if nbsFecpmThresholdsCorBit0to1 is non-zero and less than or equal to nbsFecpmCurrentCorBit0to1.

nbsFecpmTrapsCorBit1to0.name: nbsFecpmTrapsCorBit1to0
nbsFecpmTrapsCorBit1to0.description: Sent at the conclusion of an nbsFecpmThresholdsInterval if nbsFecpmThresholdsCorBit1to0 is non-zero and less than or equal to nbsFecpmCurrentCorBit1to0.

nbsFecpmTrapsUncorWords.name: nbsFecpmTrapsUncorWords
nbsFecpmTrapsUncorWords.description: Sent at the conclusion of an nbsFecpmThresholdsInterval if nbsFecpmThresholdsUncorWords is non-zero and less than or equal to nbsFecpmCurrentUncorWords.
